00:21:45,799 --> 00:21:50,500
if that has gone well, and what of the Misty Forest.

538
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,900
All right, let's drop some news bombs on these peeps.

539
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:54,700
Let's go.

540
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,799
He leads you down the hallway that you've

541
00:21:56,799 --> 00:21:58,299
walked down a few times.

542
00:21:58,299 --> 00:22:00,799
And normally, the doors are closed

543
00:22:00,799 --> 00:22:04,500
and you hear like a rumble of argument and chaos

544
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:07,299
behind these doors, at least the last time you came.

545
00:22:07,299 --> 00:22:11,000
This time, the doors are open a crack

546
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,700
and it seems quiet.

547
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:16,299
It seems almost silent.

548
00:22:16,299 --> 00:22:19,000
You hear a few stirs of chairs and you

549
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,799
enter and beyond the doors, you

550
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:29,000
see the council all seemingly silent in thought,

551
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,900
kind of looking off into different corners

552
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:38,200
and not entirely all there, but Leosin

553
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,900
makes a little rap on the door.

554
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:44,500
Well, this is the story.

555
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,799
Does a cool guy knock like Flint does.

556
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:47,600
Yeah.

557
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,600
Everyone, as if jarred from whatever stupor

558
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,799
they were in, look up and you

559
00:22:52,799 --> 00:22:55,600
see a bit of relief wash over their face

560
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:57,299
as you enter the room.

561
00:22:57,299 --> 00:23:00,799
Leosin makes the announcement that you have all returned

562
00:23:00,799 --> 00:23:04,299
and have news from the previous missions

563
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,200
that you were sent on and says,

564
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,900
I will leave you to it.

565
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:11,500
If you need anything from me before you leave,

566
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:14,500
please swing on by.

567
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:18,100
And Lady Laryl Silverhand ushers you to sit

568
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,900
at some empty chairs at the table there

569
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:23,200
and she says, dear adventurers,

570
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,100
it is good to see you back.

571
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:28,200
What can you tell us of your journeys?

572
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:33,800
We went to the Misty Forest and we found Narenvain.

573
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:35,400
Is King Melandric there?

574
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,900
Yes, King Melandric is there

575
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:41,500
and he sits up and he says, yes, you found my son?

576
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,900
Oh yeah, I don't know if you want to call him that anymore.

577
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:46,400
That bastard's riding around on a green dragon

578
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:49,000
destroying elven villages.

579
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:53,000
You see a rage well up inside.

580
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,200
He was angry the last time with just

581
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,600
about everybody who was in the room.

582
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,400
But this time you see just this silent,

583
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:05,800
seething anger and his pale compLexion

584
00:24:05,799 --> 00:24:09,399
grows a bright fiery red and he says,

585
00:24:09,399 --> 00:24:15,500
so he's with the cult of the dragon?

586
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:15,700
Yes.

587
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:18,899
I mean, to be a hundred percent honest with you,

588
00:24:18,899 --> 00:24:21,700
I'm not sure if he's with the cult or not,

589
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:25,000
but he's definitely with a dragon named Cuth

590
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:28,200
and they're laying some shit down on people.

591
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,500
Oh, I have a journal.

592
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,000
Go for it.

593
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,299
Okay, I pull out of my regular bag,

594
00:24:33,299 --> 00:24:36,299
not of holding, but it does hold things.

595
00:24:36,299 --> 00:24:38,099
My bag of hold things.

596
00:24:38,099 --> 00:24:40,899
Oh, yeah.

597
00:24:40,899 --> 00:24:43,000
And I walk over to King Melandric

598
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:46,899
and I place the journal in front of him

599
00:24:46,899 --> 00:24:49,299
and I say, do not take our word for it.

600
00:24:49,299 --> 00:24:51,500
See for yourself.

601
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,299
Read for yourself.

602
00:24:53,299 --> 00:24:53,500
Sure.

603
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,500
Take a look at this.

604
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,899
Check this out.

605
00:24:56,899 --> 00:24:59,599
You see him hold his hand on the book

606
00:24:59,599 --> 00:25:01,599
and then skim past a few pages

607
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,500
and he, as you look,

608
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:05,600
you see some of the pages that you have read

609
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:08,900
where he's mentioned that in fact,

610
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:14,800
the dragon mask that he had is at the well of the dragons

611
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:17,800
and that the cult of the dragon steps towards

612
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:20,600
becoming the power that it needs to be

613
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:23,700
or the pieces are being put into place

614
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:27,400
and the red in his face begins to fade

615
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:30,700
to more of an ashen gray

616
00:25:30,799 --> 00:25:33,400
and he just looks sick.

617
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:37,400
I tentatively and then firmly lay a hand on his shoulder

618
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:41,200
and I say, I'm sorry.

619
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:44,700
It is not your fault.

620
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:47,600
Thank you though.

621
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:50,700
My son disappeared.

622
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:51,600
Let's be honest.

623
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,500
He was exiled a long time ago.

624
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,799
He didn't disappear.

625
00:25:54,799 --> 00:25:58,400
Yeah, we kind of figured.

626
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:02,100
But this and you see him flip past more pages

627
00:26:02,100 --> 00:26:03,900
talking about King Melandric

628
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:08,500
and how he's thought less upon by Naren Vane

629
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:11,100
and how he's a poor old man.

630
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:13,400
You see different phrases skim by

631
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,600
and how he's going to be taught a lesson

632
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,700
and he shakes his head and slams the book shut

633
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:23,300
and he says, I could not have seen this coming

634
00:26:23,299 --> 00:26:28,599
and I mean, there were signs that he was not

635
00:26:28,599 --> 00:26:30,399
all we expected of him.

636
00:26:30,399 --> 00:26:34,299
But we hoped, hoped for more.

637
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:38,700
Hey there.

638
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,200
I'm your Dungeon Master, Russ More.

